<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-31T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-31T12:00:00-05:00" n="172" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3777: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1" type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-01T01:00:00+08:00">February 1, 1932—1
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 31—2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Japanese Consul General has just informed me that the Chinese has [<hi rend="italic">have</hi>] begun attack on the Japanese positions.
                            Chinese Mayor <pb facs="0257" n="153" xml:id="pg_153"/> reports that
                            Japanese started attacking at 11:30. Truce no longer obtains. Rush
                            supplemental naval forces.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to the Legation and Nanking.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_CES1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>